explanation: The solution constructs a directed graph from the given pairs and finds a node with an out-degree that is one more than its in-degree as the starting point. It then performs a depth-first search (DFS) from this starting node, backtracking and adding edges to the result in reverse order. Finally, it reverses the result and swaps the start and end of each pair to obtain a valid arrangement.

